—ЩParchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/commands/docs/generate.mdЩ@84ce94e564ea7d1453b6204e1b2aab502ca30869c4f1f424ac8e58655a129f51Їtitle: generate‘ЁExamplesЪ›Generate a sequence of numbers
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> generate {|i| if $i <= 10 { {out: $i, next: ($i + 2)} }} 0
в•­в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”¬в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв•®
в”‚ 0 в”‚  0 в”‚
в”‚ 1 в”‚  2 в”‚
в”‚ 2 в”‚  4 в”‚
в”‚ 3 в”‚  6 в”‚
в”‚ 4 в”‚  8 в”‚
в”‚ 5 в”‚ 10 в”‚
в•°в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”ґв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв•Ї


```
Generate a continuous stream of Fibonacci numbers
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> generate {|fib| {out: $fib.0, next: [$fib.1, ($fib.0 + $fib.1)]} } [0, 1]


```
Generate a continuous stream of Fibonacci numbers, using default parameters
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> generate {|fib=[0, 1]| {out: $fib.0, next: [$fib.1, ($fib.0 + $fib.1)]} }


```
Generate a running sum of the inputs
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 1..5 | generate {|e, sum=0| let sum = $e + $sum; {out: $sum, next: $sum} }
в•­в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”¬в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв•®
в”‚ 0 в”‚  1 в”‚
в”‚ 1 в”‚  3 в”‚
в”‚ 2 в”‚  6 в”‚
в”‚ 3 в”‚ 10 в”‚
в”‚ 4 в”‚ 15 в”‚
в•°в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”ґв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв•Ї


```
’ђђЪКTitle: title: generate
Path: Examples
Content:
Generate a sequence of numbers
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> generate {|i| if $i <= 10 { {out: $i, next: ($i + 2)} }} 0
в•­в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”¬в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв•®
в”‚ 0 в”‚  0 в”‚
в”‚ 1 в”‚  2 в”‚
в”‚ 2 в”‚  4 в”‚
в”‚ 3 в”‚  6 в”‚
в”‚ 4 в”‚  8 в”‚
в”‚ 5 в”‚ 10 в”‚
в•°в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”ґв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв•Ї


```
Generate a continuous stream of Fibonacci numbers
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> generate {|fib| {out: $fib.0, next: [$fib.1, ($fib.0 + $fib.1)]} } [0, 1]


```
Generate a continuous stream of Fibonacci numbers, using default parameters
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> generate {|fib=[0, 1]| {out: $fib.0, next: [$fib.1, ($fib.0 + $fib.1)]} }


```
Generate a running sum of the inputs
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 1..5 | generate {|e, sum=0| let sum = $e + $sum; {out: $sum, next: $sum} }
в•­в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”¬в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв•®
в”‚ 0 в”‚  1 в”‚
в”‚ 1 в”‚  3 в”‚
в”‚ 2 в”‚  6 в”‚
в”‚ 3 в”‚ 10 в”‚
в”‚ 4 в”‚ 15 в”‚
в•°в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”ґв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв•Ї


```
—ЩParchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/commands/docs/generate.mdЩ@da8e0bc997a204f3c8793245f9cc887be70ab4ff24429afa015a8f930878fb85Їtitle: generate‘ҐNotesЪ`The generator closure accepts a single argument and returns a record

containing two optional keys: 'out' and 'next'. Each invocation, the 'out'

value, if present, is added to the stream. If a 'next' key is present, it is

used as the next argument to the closure, otherwise generation stops.
Additionally, if an input stream is provided, the generator closure accepts two

arguments. On each invocation an element of the input stream is provided as the

first argument. The second argument is the 
``next``
 value from the last invocation.

In this case, generation also stops when the input stream stops.
’ђђЪЊTitle: title: generate
Path: Notes
Content:
The generator closure accepts a single argument and returns a record

containing two optional keys: 'out' and 'next'. Each invocation, the 'out'

value, if present, is added to the stream. If a 'next' key is present, it is

used as the next argument to the closure, otherwise generation stops.
Additionally, if an input stream is provided, the generator closure accepts two

arguments. On each invocation an element of the input stream is provided as the

first argument. The second argument is the 
``next``
 value from the last invocation.

In this case, generation also stops when the input stream stops.
